President Trump and Vice President Pence met with representatives from the American Red Cross, Salvation Army, and Southern Baptist Disaster Relief to discuss the relief efforts in response to Hurricane Harvey. The President praised the organizations for their work in helping the affected individuals and communities. He also thanked the Governor and Lieutenant Governor of Texas for their coordination and commended the Coast Guard for their rescue efforts. The President authorized a proclamation for a national day of prayer and announced that he will be visiting Texas and Louisiana with the First Lady. The representatives from the organizations provided updates on their relief efforts and expressed their appreciation for the support they have received.